About XITE It’s our mission to share our passion for music videos with the world and invite people to experience music beyond listening: to see music.  XITE is dedicated to building the best music video experience in the world. Based in Amsterdam, XITE now reaches 100 million households across multiple territories through linear networks, interactive TV apps and on-demand streaming services. The company revolutionized the way audiences experience music videos by allowing viewers to search, like and skip through its entire catalog, enjoy channels curated by its team of music experts and create their own channel based on a genre, decade and style using our unique Mixer feature. XITE has a full music video catalog through agreements with all major and top independent music labels and distributors, and works to expand this offering every day.  About the role In your role as a Frontend Developer your task will be to bring to life new features, improvements and experiments for the XITE TV app. You’ll be working with Javascript and Lightning framework to transform product ideas into a fantastic user experience. You will be part of an Agile team working to realize the ultimate music video experience for Connected TV and Set-top-boxes. Your team is also a part of a bigger group of fellow frontend developers, who have the focus on React Native and Web development for a TV and Mobile application.

 Responsibilities


 You will be collaborating with the other Engineers to decide on the choices to be made during the development process. You will continuously deliver builds for internal and external tests in order to achieve the user experience that is appropriate for the goals of the project.
 Work closely with our QA team, act on and fix bugs, develop new features and have a big impact on the user experience.
 Assure high quality of deliverables following the best practices.
 Knowledge sharing and progress within the company.


 At least 2 years of working experience with HTML, CSS, JavaScript/Front End Frameworks;
 Good debugging skills and analytical thinking;
 Understanding of good UI/UX;
 Team player with a collaborative attitude;
 You’re obsessed with code quality and committed to making sure everything is well implemented and bug-free;
 Comfortable learning new skills, being proactive and keep up with trends in development world and evolving tech stack;
 Curious and creative;
 Excellent written and oral communication skills in English;
 You live in the Netherlands.


 Our Tech Stack

 JavaScript
 Lightning JS framework

  What working at XITE means Here at XITE we make sure you’re taken care of by providing you the opportunity to develop your career in a young, fast growing and international company. We provide a challenging work environment where you have a lot of autonomy and flexible working hours. We don’t hire assholes! All XITE’ers are different and authentic in their own way, but we all have kindness in common, as well as professionalism and an optimistic attitude. Let’s not forget - we have a passion for good music and good food. That’s why we have chef prepared lunches, Friday afternoon drinks and rooftop parties! Click here to see our benefits.  The process

 1. Apply: Apply for a role and we will contact you. 
2. HR Interview: One of our recruiters will contact you, because we'd really like to find out more about you and to see if there is a culture fit between you and XITE. During this interview you can ask all your questions about the company. 
3. Technical Assignment: This is your moment to shine and let us know what skills you offer! You get one week to make this assignment. Need more time? Not a problem, just let us know! 
4. Technical interview: With two colleagues of XITE we will dive into your Technical assignment. You can also ask all your technical questions to the team! 
5. Offer: Hopefully with our offer we can welcome you to the team of XITE!

 Up for the challenge? Then hit that ‘Apply for this Job’ button!

This is Adyen  We took an unobvious approach to starting a payments company, building a platform from scratch. Today, we're the payments platform of choice for the world's brightest companies. Our unobvious approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity, of backgrounds, cultures, and perspectives, is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business challenges are unique, we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. So no matter where you're from, who you love, or what you believe in, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen.  Mobile Security Expert  We are searching for a Mobile Security Expert that will enhance and drive security due diligence activities for our In Persons Payment (IPP) offerings. You will work closely with the different streams developing the future of payments on mobile offerings. Your job will be to advise the streams how to maintain their security posture:

What are trends in the field of mobile payments?
What are threats and risks that the IPP streams should take into consideration?
What security due diligence activities should the streams initiate to provide confidence in the security posture of the products?

Two products that you might be working on are: Tap to Pay on iPhone. With this technology, we can transform an iPhone into a payment accepting device. With Tap to Pay on iPhone our customers can accept contactless card or wallet payments.
 Next to this, you might work on "the card reader", which is the companion to a merchant's smartphone or tablet. It connects via Bluetooth Low Energy and it can be attached to the mobile device with the use of a magnet which is built into the hardware.
 You will help find and drive solutions to the above issues with freedom, creativity and both tech and security passion.
  What you will do

Analyse threat intelligence sources for IPP relevant news and trends;
Facilitate threat modelling exercises and trainings for various IPP products;
Architecture current and future IPP products;
Advise on specific implementation questions that our IPP developers have;
Organise security assessments at both hardware and software level for our IPP fleet.

  Who you are

You get excited by new technology and want to work in a high paced environment where we build the future of payments on mobile;
You are an expert in the field of Mobile Security, both in Android and iOS;
You are an expert in the field of IPP on software level, preferably in mobile payments. Experience with hardware is a plus;
You have experience in threat and risk modelling, preferably experience with STRIDE assessments;
You have experience in the following areas: Software Development Lifecycle; Mobile Security; Development Security; Security Architecture;
You are familiar with at least one of the following topics: PCI SPoC, PoS-to-Host and Host-to-Host protocols;
You are a team player that wants to maintain Adyen's security posture.

  Our Diversity, Equity and Inclusion commitments  Our unobvious approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity of backgrounds, cultures, and perspectives is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business and technical challenges are unique, we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. So no matter where you're from, who you love, or what you believe in, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen.
 Studies show that women and members of underrepresented communities apply for jobs only if they meet 100% of the qualifications. Even if you don't meet 100% of the criteria then Adyen encourages you to reconsider and apply. We look forward to your application.

Trifork Eindhoven is op zoek naar een Mobile Developer! Vertaal jij moeiteloos de laatste trends naar mooie en gebruiksvriendelijke apps? Lees dan snel verder!
Full-time / Part-time · Eindhoven
Jij bentLig jij ook altijd weken van tevoren wakker als Google en Apple het nieuwste technologische snufje aankondigt? En wordt je omgeving stiekem gillend gek als je weer over de perks van Swift en Kotlin begint? No worries, bij ons kun je je passie volledig kwijt!Met zo’n innerlijke drive ben jij namelijk precies wie we zoeken. Moeiteloos vertaal je de laatste trends naar mooie en gebruiksvriendelijke apps. En natuurlijk maak je userinterfaces die er niet alleen op je telefoon superstrak uitzien, maar ook op een iPad en tablet. Kwaliteit is key en je bent pas tevreden als je een component technisch en visueel feilloos is. Spaghetticode? Daar heb je een hartgrondige hekel aan, maar gelukkig: die ga je bij ons niet tegenkomen.Verder zie je het als een buitenkans als je je mag verdiepen in Augmented Reality, Lidar of Bluetooth LE. En ben je niet alleen up-to-date met de nieuwste features maar durf je er ook mee te experimenteren. Ja, we weten hoeveel doorzettingsvermogen, leergierigheid en gevoel voor kwaliteit dat vergt. Maar dat heb jij. En daarom willen we jou aan boord!Klein dingetje nog. Geloof jij dat je grote uitdagingen altijd samen overwint? Mooi, wij ook. Als je bij ons komt werken, werk je samen met strategen, datascientists, usability designers, front-end ontwikkelaars en solution architecten. Je hebt een direct lijntje met de back-end ontwikkelaars en werkt snel en flexibel met hen samen aan vernieuwende innovaties voor topmerken.Lijkt dit je wat? Plan hieronder een kennismaking in!
"Je maakt apps met de ultieme klantervaring"
Jij hebt

HBO werk-of denkniveau (met afgeronde Informatica of Multimedia Design opleiding);
Minimaal twee jaar ervaring in Apple en Android development met Swift en/of Kotlin;
Een sterke focus op kwaliteit, gebruiksvriendelijkheid en vormgeving;
Een intrinsieke motivatie om te blijven leren en je kennis aan te scherpen;
Ervaring met het communiceren van resultaten in een zakelijk perspectief.

Waar wij graag mee werken

